=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 106<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 9<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 377<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n| active_cases    = 262<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = 160<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [https://covid19.gob.sv/ Official Statistics - Government of El Salvador]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[El Salvador]] on 18 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Redacci\u00f3n|url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias-america-latina-51956420|title=Nicaragua y El Salvador confirman los primeros casos del nuevo coronavirus|date=2020-03-20|work=BBC News Mundo|access-date=2020-03-26|language=es}}</ref> As of 28 April 2020, El Salvador reported 377 cases, 9 deaths and 106 recoveries.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sosa|first=Eduardo|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/covid-19-el-salvador-coronavirus-positivos/700739/2020/|title=A 24 sube la cifra de contagios por coronavirus en El Salvador|date=28 March 2020|work=El Diario de Hoy|access-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live|last2=Carranza|first2=Enrique}}</ref> As of that date El Salvador had arrested more people for violating the quarantine than it had diagnosed cases of COVID-19, a total of 2,323 people had been arrested for violating quarantine orders, and 22,593 people had been tested for the virus.<ref name=\"Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19\">{{cite web |url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|agency=Gobierno de El Salvador |date= 29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, the first COVID-19 death in [[El Salvador]] was confirmed.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/el-salvador-registers-countrys-first-coronavirus-death|title=El Salvador registers country's first coronavirus death|agency=National Post |date= 31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n__TOC__\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/El Salvador medical cases chart}}\n\n=== March 2020 ===\nAs 6 March, El Salvador government declared yellow alert in the country a few hours after Costa Rica reported the first confirmed case in that country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnnespanol.cnn.com/2020/03/06/alerta-el-salvador-alerta-amarilla-por-riesgo-de-coronavirus-en-el-salvador/|title=Alerta amarilla en El Salvador por riesgo de coronavirus|last=Delcid|first=Merlin|date=2020-03-07|website=[[CNN en Espa\u00f1ol]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, after the [[World Health Organization]] classified COVID-19 as a pandemic, President [[Nayib Bukele]] declared suspension of all educative activities in public and private schools all over the country for 21 days, followed by a solicitude to the [[Legislative Assembly of El Salvador|Legislative Assembly]] of declaring [[state of emergency]] and [[state of exception]], in spite of not having any [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] confirmed cases.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/es/20200314-covid19-el-salvador-nayib-bukele-am%C3%A9rica-latina|title=Sin casos confirmados de Covid-19, El Salvador emprende dr\u00e1sticas acciones para afrontar pandemia|last=|first=|date=2020-03-14|website=[[France 24]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The Office of the Attorney for the Defense of Human Rights of El Salvador head, Apolonio Tobar, considered the actions taken by the government as \"improvised\". On 13 March, Bukele declared a [[Alert state|red alert]] on the country.<ref name=\":0\" /> As the night of 14 March, both [[decree]]s were approved, declaring state of emergency for 30 days and state of exception for 15 days, accompanied by prohibition of people circulation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/america/sociedad/el-salvador-decreta-estado-de-excepcion-para-enfrentar-la-pandemia-del-covid-19/20000013-4196124|title=El Salvador decreta el estado de excepci\u00f3n para enfrentar la pandemia del COVID-19|last=L\u00f3pez|first=Enrique|date=March 15, 2020|website=[[EFE]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voanoticias.com/a/elsalvador-coronavirus-emergencia/5329152.html|title=El Salvador declara el estado de emergencia para enfrentar COVID-19|last=|first=|date=March 14, 2020|website=[[Voice of America|Voz de Am\u00e9rica]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nON 16 March, a diplomatic dispute between El Salvador and [[Mexico]] developed when President Bukele accused the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mexico|Mexican]] government of \"being irresponsible\" allowing a dozen people with COVID-19 to board a plane bound for [[El Salvador International Airport]]. Mexican foreign secretary [[Marcelo Ebrard]] said \"all flights to El Salvador, including the one mentioned by the president [Bukele], have been cancelled\"; furthermore, Mexican deputy health minister [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]] denied the charge, and declared that tests showed the individuals in question were virus-free.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Redacci\u00f3n|first=|url=https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias-america-latina-51921109|title=La pol\u00e9mica entre El Salvador y M\u00e9xico por un vuelo con supuestos enfermos de coronavirus|date=2020-03-17|work=[[BBC Mundo|BBC News Mundo]]|access-date=2020-04-06|url-status=live|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/el-salvador-accuses-mexico-sending-223043717.html|title=Mexico rejects El Salvador accusation it let coronavirus patients board plane|last=Renteria|first=Nelson|last2=Frank Jack|first2=Daniel|date=16 March 2020|work=Yahoo News|location=[[Mexico City]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=20 March 2020|agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>\n\nPresident [[Nayib Bukele]] banned public gathering of more than 500 people, prohibited most international travellers and shut down educational institutions on 17 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/national-quarantine-in-el-salvador-to-14603/|title=National Quarantine in El Salvador to contain the spread of the COVID-19|date=17 March 2020|publisher=JD Supra|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> An infectologist who avoided the quarantine after a trip to Germany is being investigated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cnnespanol.cnn.com/2020/03/19/alerta-el-salvador-investigan-a-infectologa-que-burlo-cuarentena-tras-viaje-a-alemania/|title=Investigan a infect\u00f3loga en El Salvador que burl\u00f3 cuarentena tras viaje a Alemania|last=Delcid|first=Merlin|date=19 March 2020|work=CNN en Espa\u00f1ol|language=es|trans-title=An infectologist in El Salvador who circumvented quarantine after a trip to Germany is investigated|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, President Bukele announced the first confirmed case of COVID-19 in El Salvador, which was detected in the Hospital Nacional General \"Arturo Morales\", in [[Metap\u00e1n]]. The case was identified as a male and according to the General Direction of Migration and Foreigners (''Direcci\u00f3n General de Migraci\u00f3n y Extranjer\u00eda'') he was in Italy, where presumably he was infected<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/Lo-que-se-sabe-y-lo-que-no-sobre-el-primer-infectado-con-coronavirus-en-El-Salvador-20200319-0074.html|title=Lo que se sabe (y lo que no) sobre el primer infectado con coronavirus en El Salvador|last=Calder\u00f3n|first=Beatriz|date=March 19, 2020|website=[[La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/EN-VIVO-El-Salvador-confirma-primer-caso-de-COVID-19-20200318-0064.html |title=Primer caso de COVID-19 en El Salvador pudo haber entrado por punto ciego en Metap\u00e1n; se ha activado cerco sanitario por 48 horas en ese municipio |work=La Prensa Grafica |last=Gomez |first=R\u00e9n\u00e9 |date=18 March 2020 |access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Two more cases were confirmed on 20 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.elmundo.cr/mundo/el-salvador-confirma-2-nuevos-casos-de-covid-19/ |title=El Salvador confirma 2 nuevos casos de COVID-19 |work=elmundo.cr |date=20 March 2020 |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March 2020, El Salvador declared a 30-day curfew in response to the coronavirus crisis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/el-salvador-declares-30-day-curfew-in-response-to-coronavirus|title=El Salvador declares 30-day curfew in response to coronavirus {{!}} National Post|last=Health|first=P. M. N.|date=2020-03-22|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\nThe government set up a website on 27 March for people to consult about government aid, but it collapsed over the weekend of 28\u201329 March.\n\nOn 29 March, the Legislative Assembly approved a new decree in order to extend the exception regime for 15 days more.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/Diputados-aprueban-nuevo-decreto-para-mantener-Estado-de-excepcion-por-15-dias-mas-20200329-0058.html|title=Diputados aprueban nuevo decreto para mantener Estado de excepci\u00f3n por 15 d\u00edas m\u00e1s|last=Hern\u00e1ndez|first=Wendy|date=29 March 2020|website=[[La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\nOn Monday, 30 March, hundreds of citizens defied restrictions and went to the streets to demand the promised help.<ref>[https://sinlineamx.com/en-plena-cuarentena-salvadorenos-salen-a-la-calle-y-exigen-a-bukele-la-ayuda-que-prometio/?fbclid=IwAR3x17WiUIJFQQHuRvbf1svTqikmF6IycG_cWQQxX6DVgCyNElmWoCwXpHM En plena cuarentena; salvadore\u00f1os salen a la calle y exigen a Bukele la ayuda que prometi\u00f3] Sin Embargo, 30 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, the first COVID-19 death in [[El Salvador]] was confirmed\u2014a woman over 60 who arrived from United States on 12 March who was classified in a critical state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/america/sociedad/el-salvador-registra-su-primera-muerte-por-coronavirus/20000013-4210082|title=El Salvador registra su primera muerte por el coronavirus|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=[[EFE]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/coronavirus-primera-muerte-el-salvador/701623/2020/|title=El Salvador registra primera muerte por coronavirus|last=Tejada|first=Rossy|date=2020-03-31|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\nAs 1 April 2020, the government had established 96 centers (facilities) of quarantine, with 4,276 people being retained in them, according with the official website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://covid19.gob.sv/|title=Situaci\u00f3n Nacional COVID-19|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Furthermore, the second death was confirmed, an 89-year-old man from [[San Francisco Gotera, Moraz\u00e1n|San Francisco Gotera]], who resulted negative in the first test, but turned out positive in a second one practiced on 31 March.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/coronavirus-segunda-muerte-hospital-saldana-el-salvador/701914/2020/|title=Un hombre de 89 a\u00f1os es la segunda muerte por coronavirus en El Salvador|last=Tejada|first=Rossy|date=1 April 2020|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=1 April 2020|agency=}}</ref>\n\nAs 2 April 2020, 5 more cases were confirmed, totalizing 46 cases in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/El-Salvador-reporta-cinco-casos-mas-de-COVID-19-y-eleva-cifra-global-a-46-infectados-un-contagiado-se-detecto-en-Lourdes-20200402-0113.html|title=El Salvador reporta cinco casos m\u00e1s de COVID-19 y eleva cifra global a 46 infectados: un contagiado se detect\u00f3 en Lourdes|last=Tejada|first=Rossy|date=1 April 2020|website=[[La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, the government confirmed the third death\u2014 a 60-year-old man who returned from the United States on 14 March, showing symptoms for COVID-19 and turned out positive on 30 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/america/sociedad/el-salvador-suma-su-tercera-muerte-por-covid-19-un-hombre-que-llego-de-ee-uu/20000013-4213236|title=El Salvador suma su tercera muerte por COVID-19, un hombre que lleg\u00f3 de EE.UU.|last=Redaction|date=4 April 2020|website=[[EFE]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 April, the first two recovered patients were reported by the government. A 37-year-old man who arrived from Italy and a 46-man who arrived from Spain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/coronavirus-pacientes-recuperados-el-salvador/702811/2020/|title=Dos de los pacientes confirmados de coronavirus est\u00e1n recuperados, seg\u00fan Gobierno|last=Hern\u00e1ndez|first=Nancy|date=2020-04-04|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April, President Bukele announced the obliged home quarantine will be extended for 15 days more starting from 20 April, this is because the last quarantine term would terminate on 19 April. President Bukele said he ordered the police to be \"more strict\" in order to guarantee the measures taken by the government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/es/20200407-el-salvador-extender%C3%A1-por-15-d%C3%ADas-la-cuarentena-por-el-coronavirus|title=El Salvador extender\u00e1 por 15 d\u00edas la cuarentena por el coronavirus|last=|first=|date=2020-04-07|website=[[France 24]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> The government also announced they have registered until that day 78 COVID-19 confirmed cases, also reporting one more death and three recoveries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/presidente-bukele-cuarentena-coronavirus-casos-el-salvador/703498/2020/|title=Gobierno extiende por 15 d\u00edas m\u00e1s la cuarentena domiciliar obligatoria|last=Tejada|first=Rossy|date=2020-04-06|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> Furthermore, the fourth death was reported by the government\u2014 a 41-year-old man who arrived from Guatemala on 15 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/coronavirus-cuarta-muerte-pacientes-recuperados-el-salvador/703373/2020/|title=Un hombre de 41 a\u00f1os que ingres\u00f3 de Guatemala es la cuarta muerte por coronavirus|last=Rossy|first=Tejada|last2=Hern\u00e1ndez|first2=Evelia|date=2020-04-06|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 April, the fifth death was confirmed, a 69-year-old male surgeon who arrived the country from Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/medicos-quinta-muerte-pacientes-el-salvador-coronavirus/704007/2020/|title=Un m\u00e9dico cirujano es la quinta v\u00edctima mortal por coronavirus en El Salvador|last=Hern\u00e1ndez|first=Evelia|date=2020-04-08|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, the government reported a sixth death.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/nacional/covid-19-el-salvador-coronavirus-victima/704344/2020/|title=El Salvador reporta la sexta v\u00edctima mortal por coronavirus|last=Carranza|first=Enrique|date=2020-04-09|website=[[El Diario de Hoy]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn April 11, the government inaugurated two hospitals: the first one in Jiquilisco and the second in Tecoluca, with the purpose of attending up to 500 COVID-19 infected people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us.as.com/us/2020/04/12/tikitakas/1586720002_098236.html|title=El Salvador inaugura dos hospitales para combatir coronavirus|last=Cort\u00e9s Luna|first=Carlos|date=2020-04-12|website=[[Diario AS|AS USA]]|language=es-us|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/Coronavirus-en-El-Salvador-asi-son-los-2-nuevos-hospitales-que-atenderan-a-pacientes-contagiados-en-Tecoluca-y-Jiquislisco--20200411-0024.html|title=Coronavirus en El Salvador: as\u00ed son los 2 nuevos hospitales que atender\u00e1n a pacientes contagiados en Tecoluca y Jiquislisco|last=Sibri\u00e1n|first=Walter|date=April 11, 2019|website=La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn April 15, the [[International Monetary Fund]] announced the approval of 389 million dollars to El Salvador, with the purpose of strengthening the most affected places of the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voanoticias.com/a/elsalvador-fmi-aprueba-millonario-financiamiento-/5372609.html|title=FMI aprueba millonario financiamiento para El Salvador por pandemia|last=Castro|first=Lenny|date=2020-04-15|website=[[Voice of America|Voz de Am\u00e9rica]]|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn April 16 the Supreme Court of El Salvador ruled that the government couldn't confiscate vehicles, property or arrest people for allegedly failing to comply with quarantine order without congressional legislation approving the measures. Bukele stated his intentions to defy the ruling. Over 2,000 people had already been arrested for violations of quarantine restrictions.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-el-salvador/el-salvadors-president-disregards-top-court-rulings-on-coronavirus-idUSKCN21Y0IA |title=El Salvador's president disregards top court rulings on coronavirus |date=April 16, 2020 |work=Reuters}}</ref> Also, the seventh death was reported by the government, a 4-year-old child who died on Hospital Bloom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/Muere-nino-de-4-anos-por-coronavirus-en-Hospital-Bloom-y-ponen-en-cuarentena-al-personal-de-Salud-familia-y-vecinos-20200416-0105.html|title=Muere ni\u00f1o de 4 a\u00f1os por coronavirus en Hospital Bloom y ponen en cuarentena al personal de Salud, familia y vecinos|last=G\u00f3mez, Ren\u00e9; Calderon, Beatriz; Alem\u00e1n, Francisco; Vel\u00e1squez, Mirna|first=|date=2020-04-16|website=[[La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn April 22, the government confirmed the eight death, a 62-year-old man who arrived from the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laprensagrafica.com/elsalvador/Reportan-octavo-fallecido-por-covid-19-en-El-Salvador-se-trata-de-un-hombre-de-62-anos--20200422-0074.html|title=Reportan octavo fallecido por covid-19 en El Salvador: se trata de un hombre de 62 a\u00f1os|last=Sibri\u00e1n|first=Walter|date=2020-04-22|website=[[La Prensa Gr\u00e1fica]]|language=es-ES|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n==Charts==\n=== Curves of infection and deaths ===\nThe graphs show the development of the pandemic starting from 18 March 2020, the day when the first case was detected in Metap\u00e1n.\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=700\n|height=250\n|colors=#FF6347,#FFC000,#87CEEB,#A50026\n|showValues=\n|xType=date\n|xAxisFormat=%b %e\n<!-- PLease clipboard copy the \"}x=...\" and \"y1=...\" lines from the log plot of total cases when you update these charts -->\n\n<!-- Search string CASES_X -->\n|x= 2020/03/18, 2020/03/19, 2020/03/20, 2020/03/21, 2020/03/22, 2020/03/23, 2020/03/24, 2020/03/25, 2020/03/26, 2020/03/27, 2020/03/28, 2020/03/29, 2020/03/30, 2020/03/31, 2020/04/01, 2020/04/02, 2020/04/03